quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  3,166,"And what befell you the day when the two armies met, it was by Allah´s permission; that He might know the true believers"
  3,167,"And He might know those who are hypocrites; for it was said to them, \"Come, fight in Allah´s way,\" or \"Repel (the foe)\" But they said, \"If we knew how to fight we would surely follow you.\" They were that day far nearer"
  3,168,"Those who said of their brethren, whilst they themselves stayed at home, \"Had they been guided by us they would not have been killed.\" Say (unto them), \"Then repel from yourselves death, if you are truthful"
  3,169,"Think not those who are slain in the way of Allah as dead. Nay, they are living; with their Lord they have sustenance"
  3,170,"Rejoicing in what Allah has brought them of His Bounty, glad for those who have not reached them yet, those left behind; there is no fear for them, and they shall not grieve"
  3,171,"They rejoice at the favour from Allah and grace, and that Allah wastes not the wages of the believers"
  3,172,"Whoever answered to the call of Allah and of His Prophet after sorrow had befallen them, for those, if they do good and fear evil, there is a great reward"
  3,173,"Those unto whom men said, \"Verily, men have gathered against you, therefore, fear them,\" but it only increased their faith, and they say, \"Allah is enough for us. He is the Most Excellent Disposer of affairs"